# Purpl Brain Protocol

The MCP server `purpl-brain` exposes four tools. Use them as first-class actions, not optional helpers.

## Session start ‚Äî required before writing any code

Call `brain_query` before touching any file or making any recommendation:

- `query`: what are the most recent decisions and open questions for <area of work>?
- `project_id`: skalrn_purpl_brain

Do not proceed without loading context ‚Äî the brain may have a constraint you don't know about.

## Before answering design-intent questions ‚Äî required

Any question about whether, why, when, or how to change the system should be preceded by `brain_query` if the topic touches ingestion, workers, the brain store, query layer, API routes, or data schemas.

Skip if the brain was already queried on the same topic earlier in this session.

## Before significant implementation ‚Äî required

Before any change touching ingestion workers, the brain store, query layer, API routes, or data schemas, call `brain_analyze_impact`:

- `change_description`: plain-English description of what you are about to change
- `project_id`: skalrn_purpl_brain

## When a decision is made ‚Äî call immediately

Call `brain_log_decision` the moment a significant choice is made. Do not defer to session end.

Significant decisions include:
- Choosing a library, pattern, or approach over alternatives
- Deciding NOT to do something
- Discovering a constraint or edge case that will affect future work

**Note:** Cursor has no Stop hook. There is no automated reminder at session end. You must call `brain_log_decision` mid-session as decisions are made. The API will reject entries where `rationale` is empty or descriptions are too short ‚Äî retry with fuller content if you receive a 422.

## When something unexpected surfaces ‚Äî call immediately

If you discover something that contradicts a past decision, call `brain_log_signal` before continuing.

## Tool parameter reference

**`brain_query`** ‚Äî `query` (string), `project_id` (string), optional `mode` ("project" | "expertise" | "agent_resume")

**`brain_log_decision`** ‚Äî `project_id`, `session_id` (timestamp-slug or UUID), `work_completed` (string), `decisions` (array of `{id, description, rationale, alternatives_considered?, confidence?}`)

**`brain_analyze_impact`** ‚Äî `change_description` (string), `project_id` (string)

**`brain_log_signal`** ‚Äî `text` (string), `project_id` (string), optional `source` ("agent" | "github" | "slack" | "jira" | "meeting" | "document")
